<h1 id="toc16"><span>Achievement Badges</span></h1>
<h3 id="toc17"><span>Badges from the <a href="/scp-achievement-badges">SCP Achievement Badges</a> page.</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Certificate Of Attendance:</strong> Post an Author Page, add to a Collaborative Log, and participate in an Official SCP Wiki Contest.</li>
<li><strong>Draw Me Like One Of Your [REDACTED]:</strong> Create an artwork page with a rating of at least +30.</li>
<li><strong>Participation Trophy:</strong> Write an article rated at least +100.</li>
<li><strong>Straight Out Of Central Casting:</strong> Create a character who merits their own tag and has been featured in works by 3 other writers.</li>
<li><strong>Lore Expert:</strong> You've written at least 3 GOI articles and/or skips rated +50 or above.</li>
<li><strong>The Medium Is The Message:</strong> Author of at least 10 media files (images, audio, videos, etc.) that are used on the wiki. Must be original works released under a version CC-by-SA license compatible with the SCP Wiki.</li>
<li><strong>Look Ma! I'm On TV!:</strong> Have one of your works be featured on an off-site video, podcast, video game, etc.</li>
<li><strong>Level Up!:</strong> You've been a member of the SCP Wiki for one calendar year.</li>
<li><strong>Skip Tutoring:</strong> Have an SCP draft thread you gave feedback on succeed on the main list.</li>
<li><strong>Extra! Extra!:</strong> One of your articles has been featured on the front page.</li>
<li><strong>Distinguished Butterfly:</strong> Be featured on the Reviewers' Spotlight.</li>
<li><strong>Pagemaster:</strong> Contribute icons or new achievements to the SCP Achievement Badges Page.</li>
</ul>
